1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:05,990
In this video we are going to learn proxy pattern, decorator pattern and security library.

2
00:00:06,170 --> 00:00:09,020
Let me start with the what is proxy pattern?

3
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:15,350
The proxy pattern provides a placeholder for another object in order to control access to it.

4
00:00:15,380 --> 00:00:22,400
This pattern creates a proxy object that serves as an intermediary for requests intended for the original

5
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,030
object.

6
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:29,780
A common use case is like lazy loading, controlling access, logging, and so on.

7
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:37,040
It is like having a gatekeeper who can add extra behavior or checks before accessing the actual object.

8
00:00:37,810 --> 00:00:40,270
The next pattern is decorator pattern.

9
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:45,850
The decorator pattern dynamically adds behavior to an object without altering its structure.

10
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:52,360
It involves a set of decorator classes that are used to extend the functionality of the original class

11
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:59,500
without changing its code, and decorator pattern is useful for adding functionalities to objects at

12
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:06,550
runtime, for example, enhancing a window object with additional features like borders scrollbars dynamically.

13
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:11,200
So how can we use decorator pattern and how we can implement it?

14
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:17,080
The first step is we can create abstract decorators that implement the same interface as the object.

15
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:22,210
They will extend and then concrete decorator classes add additional behavior.

16
00:01:22,210 --> 00:01:28,750
For example, if you have a basket repository class for database operation, you can create a cased

17
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:33,550
basket repository that extends the basket repository with caching capabilities.

18
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,830
So what is security library and why we use it?

19
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:39,570
Security library is a.

20
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:44,310
Net library that extends the built in IOC container of ASP.Net core.

21
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:50,100
It provides additional capabilities to scan and register services in more flexible ways.

22
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:57,330
Security library also particularly useful for implementing patterns like decorator in a clean and manageable

23
00:01:57,330 --> 00:01:57,780
way.

24
00:01:57,810 --> 00:02:04,110
It simplifies the process of service registration and decoration in ASP.Net core applications.

25
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:08,880
So how can we implement these decorator pattern using the security library?

26
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:11,009
I'm going to explain step by step.

27
00:02:11,009 --> 00:02:14,850
The first step is define interface and base implementation.

28
00:02:14,850 --> 00:02:16,950
We can start with an interface.

29
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:23,460
For example I basket repository and a base implementation which is the basket repository that communicate

30
00:02:23,460 --> 00:02:24,510
with the database.

31
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,420
And after that we can create decorator class.

32
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:34,440
So in the second step we can create a decorator class like cased basket repository that also implements

33
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,730
a basket repository.

34
00:02:35,730 --> 00:02:39,390
But adding the caching logic and business inside of this class.

35
00:02:40,210 --> 00:02:44,050
And the last step is register services with Secretor.

36
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:51,580
We can use Secretor library in Program.cs to first register the Base Services basket repository, and

37
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:54,940
then they apply the decorator one, which is the cache basket repository.

38
00:02:54,970 --> 00:02:57,160
You can see the code on the slide.

39
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:58,510
The first line of code.

40
00:02:58,510 --> 00:03:02,530
We can register a basket repository with the actual basket repository.

41
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:07,720
But after that we can decorate these basket repository with using the Secretor library.

42
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:13,150
In the decorate method, we can decorate the basket repository with the case basket repository, including

43
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:14,470
the cache capabilities.

44
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:21,730
That means we can say that the decorator pattern and Secretor library offers a robust approach to extending

45
00:03:21,730 --> 00:03:25,180
the functionality of services in ASP.Net core applications.

46
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:31,780
So now we will develop cased basket repository with proxy decorator patterns and security library.

